#Every year, tens of thousands of dollars in grant funding for students goes unclaimed. There are students that need access to grant funds in order to complete their studies, and there are grantors that wish to give out these funds, but students (grant applicants) don't know about the grants available and so do not apply for these unknown grants. Grantors are unable to give out these funds each acacemic year because either no one or very few applicants applied. Our application would look at student data, grant data, and then determine if a student has met the qualifications for teh grant, and if so, automatically apply them to the grant. If there is something additional needed by the grant application, such as an essay or portfolio, the application would send the auto-filled information to the student in an email in addition to a reminder letting them know to write the essay and then submit the application to the email address or link provided. This would allow for students to obtain needed funds to complete their research or education and studies, and for grantors to be able give out the funds.
